General Comments:
The most interesting part of this lab was managing the array of pointers. 
It was a good challenge to ensure that the favorites list did not need its 
own copies of the strings, but rather just pointed to the memory already 
allocated for the primary book list. Dealing with the newline character 
left in the buffer by scanf was a small issue for me. Implementing the 
lab3.h file helped organize the function prototypes cleanly.

GDB Debugging Report:
To verify my program, I used GDB to ensure memory was being allocated 
correctly for each book title. I set a breakpoint at the line where strcpy 
runs and used the print command to inspect the buffer and the book_list[i] 
pointer. I stepped through the loop using next to verify that each subsequent 
title was being stored in a unique memory address. By printing book_list[i] 
after allocation, I confirmed that the memory addresses were distinct and 
that no data was being overwritten.